<db:para><db:emphasis>Qt Linguist</db:emphasis> is a tool for translating strings in Qt applications. Once you have installed Qt, you can start <db:emphasis>Qt Linguist</db:emphasis> in the same way as any other application on the development host.</db:para>
<db:para>To address issues that arise from the subtleties and complexities of human language, translators and developers may need to:</db:para>
<db:itemizedlist>
<db:listitem>
<db:para>Translate a single phrase into several different forms depending on context. For example, <db:emphasis>open</db:emphasis> in English might become <db:emphasis>&#246;</db:emphasis><db:emphasis>ffnen</db:emphasis>, <db:emphasis>open file</db:emphasis>, or <db:emphasis>aufbauen</db:emphasis>, <db:emphasis>open internet connection</db:emphasis>, in German.</db:para>
</db:listitem>
<db:listitem>
<db:para>Change the mnemonic characters in keyboard shortcuts without introducing conflicts. For example, <db:code>\&amp;Quit</db:code> in English becomes <db:emphasis>Avslutt</db:emphasis> in Norwegian, which does not contain the letter <db:emphasis>Q</db:emphasis>. You cannot use a letter that is already in use unless you change several shortcuts.</db:para>
</db:listitem>
<db:listitem>
<db:para>Rephrase strings that contain variables. For example, you might need to place the variables in a different order when you translate the string <db:emphasis>The 25 files selected will take 63 seconds to process</db:emphasis>, where the two numbers are inserted programmatically at runtime.</db:para>
</db:listitem>
</db:itemizedlist>
